<% provide(:title, "Log in") %> 

<h1>Log in</h1> 
<div class="row"> 
  <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3"> 
  <%= form_with(url: login_path, scope: :session, local: true) do |f| %> 
    <%= f.label :email %> 
    <%= f.email_field :email, class: 'form-control' %> 
    <%= f.label :password %> <%= f.password_field :password, class: 'form-control' %> 
    <%= f.submit "Log in", class: "btn btn-primary" %> 
  <% end %> 
  
  <p>New user? <%= link_to "Sign up now!", signup_path %></p> 
  </div>
</div>

<p>
  This is the Log In page for anyone that has already created an Organizational
  Account.  Currently, there is no benefit to logging in and logging out except
  seeing your user profile name with a default Gravatar image to the left of it.
</p>

<p>
  Eventually, you will be able edit your organization's description, name, contact
  information, profile photo.  You will also be able to add volunteering opportunities
  linked to your organization when you are logged in as an organization.  You
  currently cannot delete an account or change your password, but eventually you
  will.  Ideally, creating and deleting organizational accounts will be done
  with permissions from an administrating user account held by Connecting 
  Grinnellians personnell.
</p>

